subject: MSN-list Digest, Vol 7, Issue 102
body: 2 (return) [ Ausonius was successively promoted to the Prætorian præfecture of Italy, (A.D. 377,) and of Gaul, (A.D. 378;) and was at length invested with the consulship, (A.D. 379.) He expressed his gratitude in a servile and insipid piece of flattery, (Actio Gratiarum, p. 699-736,) which has survived more worthy productions.]
